title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1972-09-21
lineage: DAT (Tascam DA-40) > Tascam DA-3000 > Samplitude Pro X5 Suite > FLAC
description:
Set I
Promised Land, Bird Song, El Paso, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Black Throated Wind, Big Railroad Blues, Jack Straw, Loser, Big River, Ramble On Rose, Cumberland Blues, Playin' In The Band
Set II
He's Gone, Truckin', Black Peter, Mexicali Blues, Dark Star-> Mind Left Body Jam -> Morning Dew, Beat It On Down The Line, Mississippi Half Step, Sugar Magnolia, Friend Of The Devil, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Transitive Diamonds Another in a string of anniversary listens for me today.  I’m pleased but not surprised to report that 51 years later this show remains a signature night of GD music, highlighted by a terrific, sweeping Dark Star, particularly the final priceless jam I call “the battle of Goin’ Down the Road vs Sugar Mag”, a GD struggle for transition supremacy, resolving into a sweet MLB jam with a hint of Dear Prudence notes thrown in at the end for good measure. Jerry finally settles things and leads a beautiful spin of Morning Dew. O’h, and both Sugar Mag and GDTRFB appear later in the set, so everybody wins. Indeed.
